    "LogState_SolveDes_1" : "!1uy! You can ask laborers to gather wild vegetables or place orders with the merchant ships to get food more quickly. The Hunters Hut, Gatherers Hut, and Fishing Dock produce food each month. Fields, Orchards, and Pastures have high yields but require a long time to mature before they can be harvested.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_10" : "!1uz! Keep an eye on Domestic Fuel reserves and ensure warehouses are not too far away from residential areas.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_11" : "!1v0! You can manually choose to enable or disable of a structure, but remember, you will need to assign workers again to the work after re-enable the structure.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_12" : "!1v1! New warehouses are required for storage.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_13" : "!1v2! No formula has been selected. You must select a product for the structure.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_14" : "!1v3! You must assign more workers to this profession.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_15" : "!1v4! Keep an eye on material reserves and ensure warehouses are not too far away from houses and processing type buildings.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_16" : "!1v5! You must adjust the output limit to allow production to continue.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_17" : "!1v6! This structure cannot be used after reserves are exhausted. Remember to dismiss the workers in the structure.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_18" : "!1v7! You can use the Cancel command to abort the demolition.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_19" : "!1v8! Pay attention to the number of repairmen to avoid structures being damaged.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_2" : "!1v9! You can ensure the supply of drinking water by constructing wells and assigning water fetchers to gather it. You can also use coins to order drinking water.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_20" : "!1va! A ruined building needs to be rebuilt by the builders.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_21" : "!1vb! Can be manually enabled or disabled.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_22" : "!1vc! Fires can only be put out if there are wells nearby. Changing the policy can change the firefighting method.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_23" : "!1vd! Prioritizing new events will lower the priority of previous ones.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_24" : "!1ve! Keep an eye on fertility rates. And you can postpone building houses if they are already more than enough for the use of next generation.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_25" : "!1vf! You can reassign farmers to temporarily assist with other work.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_26" : "!1vg! Tech Points can be used in Technology panel.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_27" : "!1vh! In the early stages, the Gatherers Hut can be used as a source of Herbs. Later, obtaining herb seeds through trade or tech will allow you to grow large amounts of Herbs in the Nursery.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_28" : "!1vi! Timber can be acquired by cutting down trees. But you can have higher outputs in Forest Farms.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_29" : "!1vj! Stone can be collected in the wild, but mining at a Quarry is more efficient and has a higher output.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_3" : "!1vk! Produce enough clothing and Domestic Fuel can keep citizens warm.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_30" : "!1vl! Fuel can be obtained by processing Timber at the Chopping House. Or you can have a higher output in the Sawmill.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_31" : "!1vm! You can reappoint or replace the administrators at the Town Hall.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_32" : "!1vn! A Pasture or Corral is required to raise animals.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_33" : "!1vo! A Field, Nursery or Plantation is needed to grow crops.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_34" : "!1vp! A Dock is required for the merchant ship to stop at.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_35" : "!1vq! A Town Hall is required for the immigrants to be accepted in town.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_36" : "!1vr! All field crops in will be harvested in the autumn.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_37" : "!1vs! New houses are required for citizens to live in.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_38" : "!1vt! Repairmen are needed to maintain your town's structures.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_39" : "!1vu! Cancel some citizens' work to make them laborers.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_4" : "!1vv! Constructing houses or Interim Housings can solve this problem, however ordinary Interim Housings affect citizens' desire to have children.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_40" : "!1vw! Tailors make clothing and backpacks. Basic clothing protects citizens in the winter and allows them to work outside, reducing their chances of freezing to death.\n      Advanced clothing also increases happiness, though you will need to upgrade the Tailors to unlock advanced tailoring techniques. Advanced tailors can make all kinds of clothing.\n      Backpacks allow citizens to carry more weight and largely increase transportation efficiency.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_5" : "!1vx! Clinics and hospitals can treat citizens with diseases.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_6" : "!1vy! Tools can be produced by constructing a blacksmith's. The ordering function of trade can be quickly obtained through the use of silver coins.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_7" : "!1vz! Click the event bar to view or adjust citizens' professions, adjusting the number of workers a profession as required.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_8" : "!1w0! Keep an eye on food reserves and ensure warehouses are not too far away from residential areas.",
    "LogState_SolveDes_9" : "!1w1! Keep an eye on water reserves and ensure warehouses are not too far away from residential areas.",
